The markings on the Grimmace&rsquo;s body begin to appear as it ages and takes the weight of the world on its back. The Grimmace is a creature that is a mistake, in a sense. It was never meant to be, yet man created it with all of the pain and suffering and sin that is in this world. If people would stop the pain, the Grimmace may no longer be. It is also a very feared creature for its size and dark markings, but the truth is that because the Grimmace has seen so many bad things, it is joyful most of the time. It cannot stand to see people fight. So, it stops them by interfering and scaring them away. The abomination that is the Grimmace must be preserved, yet must never reproduce again, for when it does, it means that more pain is happening somewhere in the world.
Credits are given to Penguinman for &ldquo;slight help.&rdquo;
This download has no known issues and includes a gift for guests to purchase.

From the Zoopedia as written by Hendrix and Monschatten:
&ldquo;To unlock the unicorn in challenge oder campaign the zoo needs a 5-star rating.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Today, Unicorns are mostly illustrated as white horses with a single horn on the forehead. But this is not correct. The best idea of the unicorn&rsquo;s appearence can be found on gobelins. They show the unicorn as a deer-like artiodactyl. It has a slender neck with a long mane and a slim head. The horn is high on the forehead above the eyes. It consists of ivory and is twisted like a spiral. The ears are larger than those of a horse. Under the chin the unicorn has a beard like a goat.&rdquo;

Note: this is an ambient, not an adoptable animal. This means it will spawn in the environment at random intervals.
